The paper discusses the design and implementation of a programming language with a novel variant of effect handlers, which is a topic related to programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also presents a formal account of the type system and semantics of the language, which is related to logic in computer science (cs.LO) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also introduces a novel form of effect polymorphism, which is related to formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL) and type theory (cs.TYPES).
